HEADWORD: Guicowar
<hw>Gui"co*war</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>[Mahratta
<ets>g⟦amac⟧ekw⟦amac⟧r</ets>, prop., a cowherd.] The title of the
sovereign of Guzerat, in Western India; -- generally called the
<altname>Guicowar of Baroda</altname>, which is the capital of the
country.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

